Consider the system of differential equations:
\begin{align*}
\frac{dx}{dt} &= -x + 2y - x^3 \\
\frac{dy}{dt} &= -x - y + y^3
\end{align*}

Given an initial condition $(x_0, y_0) = (1, 2)$, find the solution to this system of equations over the time interval $t \in [0, 10]$. Use a computer or software package to graph the solution. Then, determine whether the solution approaches a steady state or exhibits chaotic behavior.
